#### docstext ####
text: Note, we do not support submitting a record to multiple communities in one go. Instead, simply repeat the recipe below.

#### docsheader ####
text: Submit to community
----
ref:submit
#### docsstep ####
step: 1
----
text: Go to the record you want to submit to a community and click the cog-wheel icon to open the communities menu.
----
image: record.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Click **Submit to community** in the dropdown menu.
----
image: menu.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 3
----
text: Find the community you want to submit to and click the **Select** button.
----
image: dialog.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 4
----
text: Confirm you want to submit the record to the community by:

- Ticking the checkbox that curators gain view and edit access to your record.
- Optionally, write a message to the curators.

Finally, click the blue **Submit to community** button.
----
image: confirm.png

#### docsheader ####
text: View pending submission
----
ref:pending
#### docsstep ####
step: 1
----
text: Click **Pending submissions** in the community dropdown menu from the record landing page.
----
image: menu.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Click the community title to view the access request.
----
image: pending.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 3
----
text: The access request allows you to have a conversation with the community curators. See also [manage submission](../manage-submissions/) for further details.
----
image: request.png
